  <module>neptune</module>
  <modulesummary>neptune command</modulesummary>
  <description>
    <p>neptune is a tool whose sole purpose is to write greetings binary
    string greetings to IO.</p>
  </description>
  <section>
    <marker id="command_line"></marker>
    <title>Using neptune</title>
    <p>neptune takes an integer and returns a greeting from neptune returning
    the square of the integer supplied.</p>
    <p><em>Exit status:</em></p>
      <taglist>
        <tag><c>0</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>Processed successfully.</p>
        </item>
        <tag><c>1</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>An error occurred</p>
        </item>
      </taglist>
      <code type="none">neptune [--version] [--square Integer]</code>
      <p><em>Options:</em></p>
      <taglist>
        <tag><c>--version</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>Print the neptune version and exit.</p>
        </item>
        <tag><c>--square Integer</c></tag>
        <item>
          <p>Calculate the square of the integer and return that information
	  as a greeting from neptune.</p>
        </item>
      </taglist>
  </section>
